title: Launch Roundup – Northrop Grumman prepare the first Cygnus to fly on Falcon 9
summary: Recent challenges with weather concerns and the movement of key flights such as USSF-52 and Axiom-3 have impacted Falcon 9 launch dates, not least Starlink Group 7-11 which scrubbed three times and is now awaiting launch on Tuesday.

title: The White House versus the private sector in space
summary: Rick Tumlinson argues that the Commercial Space Act put forth by Congress offers better NewSpace regulations than the White House.

title: Space race 2024: A critical year ahead for U.S. Space Force
summary: The U.S. Space Force enters its fifth year amid heightened threats to the nation’s space assets, rising geopolitical tensions and technological challenges.

title: NASA loses, and then recovers, contact with its historic Mars helicopter
summary: Ingenuity has been flying above Mars, off and on, for nearly three years.

title: Japan’s moon lander forced to power down but may yet be revived
summary: Japan’s SLIM lander has been forced to power down on the moon with its solar cells unable to catch sunlight, but hope remains that the spacecraft can be reactivated.
